The minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami and the executive vice chairman of Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC), Prof Umar Garba Danbatta were named among the ‘Top 10 Tech Leaders in Nigeria 2020’, by the annual World Digital Exhibition (Worldex). Others in the recognition list include the CEO of MTN Nigeria Plc, Mr Ferdinand Moolman, and the executive vice chairman of Globacom Limited, Mrs Bella Disu, Worldex is a technology trade fair that seeks to link up Sub-Saharan Africa (SSA) with the rest of the global technology community. The annual event is held in Benin City, Edo State, Nigeria. <img class="size-medium wp-image-41649 alignleft" src="https://i2.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/30da6b14-danbatta-umar-690x450.jpg?resize=300%2C196&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="300" height="196" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/30da6b14-danbatta-umar-690x450.jpg?resize=300%2C196&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/30da6b14-danbatta-umar-690x450.jpg?resize=600%2C391&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i2.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/30da6b14-danbatta-umar-690x450.jpg?resize=690%2C450&amp;ssl=1 690w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" />  The other people listed for Nigeria are Ms Funke Opeke, the CEO of MainOne Cable Nigeria Limited; Mrs. Juliet Ehimuan Chiazor, the director of Google Nigeria/West Africa; and Arc. Yusuf Kazaure, the former CEO of Galaxy Backbone Plc who is now the chairman of Nigerian Communications Satellite Limited. The rest are: Mr Leo Stan Ekeh, chairman of Zinox Technologies Limited; Mr Mitchell Elegbe, founder/CEO of Interswitch Group, and Mr John Obaro, CEO of SystemSpecs Nigeria Limited. The managing director of Alford Conferences Limited, the owner and organizer of Worldex, Engr Dennis Jamgbadi said that, “We want to use this weekly recognition program to honour and celebrate the top leaders in the ICT industry in all the 47 countries of Sub-Saharan Africa, as well as forge a greater cooperation and collaboration amongst them.”